11:
Run along home now, dearie. It's too
soon for a little darling like you to go
any farther.
24:
Even though you forgot who you
were along the way? I bet you don't
even remember your own name.
28: Unfortunately, it's time to wake up.
30:
We'll meet again someday,
Couette... Take care not to lose
yourself before our next meeting.
54:
Out of the way! That little girl is
gonna get hurtâ€”
57:
If you don't stay put, you'll be caught
in her attack!
74: They sure didn't. Dad is proud of you!
90:
Th-that was close... I don't know how
I can ever repay you!
93:
I'm sorry, that was my bad. Are you
okayâ€”
101:
Is that so? He certainly looks the
part.
103:
Well then, young lad... Take care of
my daughter Couette.
105: I'm not the most experienced, but...
116:
...You've been searching for
someone to be your mentor?
119:
Yes. I want to know more about my
power. I want to see where it leads
me.
121:
The people of this world aren't very
well versed in the ways of magic.
123:
Unlike the rigid logic and laws of
alchemy, magic often has a mind of
its own. You'd be hard pressed to
find anyone here adept in it.
125:
...Ah, but my apologies. I've been
extremely rude, haven't I? I am Elliot,
Couette's father.
127:
Er, well met, sir. But I'm confused.
What do you mean by the people of
"this world"?
130:
It's okay, you don't have to pretend.
We already know. You're all from
another world.
134:
I saw it in a dream. Our world was
one of many in a sea of stars.
141:
Indeed. But Couette's dreams are no
mere dreams. In fact, we discovered
Koma's vessel atop Couette's pillow
one morning.
142:
To be able to interact with things
outside our realm... My daughter is
truly blessed.
144:
Is that why you're searching for a
mentorâ€”to develop her power
further?
147:
Oh, not exactly. I just thought it
would be a good experience for her,
should the opportunity ever present
itself.
149:
After all, how often is it that you
spend your life searching for
something and actually find it?
150:
She takes after me in that regard,
though I am nothing more than an
amateur researcher.
153:
He's just being polite. My dad's
actually an amazing alchemist.
156:
You flatter me.
Regardless, it is unfortunate that
others seek my dear Couette's
power for their own gain.
158:
I assume you're referring to the foes
you felled earlier... Indeed, leaving
for other worlds would keep her safe
from them, as an additional boon.
161:
We'd never turn away someone in
need, of course, but... I'm not sure
we're qualified to teach magic.
166:
That's okay. The worlds beyond this
one are new to me. Everything will
be a learning experience.
174: Wh-what now? I don't smell, do I?
180: So even if I'm lost in a dream...
184: Alk. Stella. Will you take me with you?
189:
Of course. We welcome you,
Couette.
194:
Take care, Couette. Don't stay up too
often, and eat all your green peas,
okay?
196:
Okay, Dad. But promise you won't
work too hard. You'll worry Mom.
199: I promise. Be well, my dear Couette.
206:
I'm going to become a wise and
powerful mage.
210:
But I can't do it by myself. I'll need
your help and guidance.
214: We'll back you up however we can!
